posts.post_title: Anyone have any extra t207s lying around?  I have plenty of tradebait!
posts.post_content:
Posted By: Brian McQueen
Thought I'd take a stab at making some progress on this set.  Looking for some cheap commons in lowgrade to get myself going but will consider any cards available.  I probably would pass on a Weaver or Lowdermilk sort of card, however, beaters and trimmed cards are always welcome with me.  

Below are the t207s I already have - all of these are Napoleon backs.  So basically I'm needing everybody else ....

Collins, Dooin, Ferry, Gardner, Gowdy, Hallinan, Henry, Hogan, Konetchy, Lapp, Nunamaker, Schardt, Severoid, Street, Strunk, Tooley, Wolverton, Yerkes


Here are some cards I'd make available for trades --

------------------------------------------
t202 Bresnahan PSA 5
t207 Yerkes (recruit) FR/GD condition
t212 1909 Obak Reidy (horizontal) w/ GHOST PRINT VG/EX
t212 1911 Obak O'Rourke PSA 3
t212 1911 Obak Lamline PSA 4
t212 1911 Obak Dillon PSA 4
e95 Maddox SGC 40
e95 Morgan SGC 30
e98 Bridwell (gr) FR- - creasing across middle/scrapes on back
e98 Mullin (bl) PR - heavy back damage, large nick on one border
e98 McLean (bl) PR - pinkish tint on front, heavy back damage
e98 Davis (bl) PR - 2 scrapes on front borders, heavy back damage
e98 Dooin (or) SGC 10 - spider wrinkles and one smaller crease
1911 Zeenut Fitzgerald SGC 30
1913 Zeenut McCorry (SF) EX - only slight touches to corners
1913 Zeenut Mitze (Oakland) VG - mild corner wear, no wrinkling, great catching pose
1913 Zeenut Mundorf (SF) VG - mild corner wear, no wrinkling
m116 Demmitt SGC 50 ("300 subjects" back)
m116 Zwilling SGC 50 ("300 subjects" back)
w519 Fatty Arbuckle EX
w553 O'Doul GD wrinkling
w572 group of four (Burns, Henline, Johnson, King) FR-GD range
------------------------------------------


Thanks guys, I appreciate the responses!
Brian
